text.tspan: Scholars note that redheads have influenced history
out of proportion to their numbers. Famous
redheads include Roman emperor Nero, Cleopatra,
Napoleon Bonaparte, Antonio Vivaldi,
Thomas Jefferson, Vincent Van Gogh, Mark Twain,
Winston Churchill, Galileo, and King David.
A 2002 study found that redheads
are harder to sedate than any other people
requiring twenty percent more anesthesia.
Mark Twain once quipped that
“While the rest of the human race
are descended from monkeys,
redheads derive from cats.”
Red hair doesn’t gray as much as
other hair colors. Red hair tends
to turn blond and then white
In Egypt, redheads were buried alive
as sacrifices to the god Osiris
The ancient Greeks believed that
redheads would turn into vampires
after they died
The most rare hair color in humans is
red. Redheads only make up about
2 to 6% of the U.S. population
According to a Clairol Color Attitude
survey, 71% of redheads think that the
word “bold” describes them.

g.text: Gingerphobia is a fear of redheads
